                          <div class="node-inner">                                    <div class="homelinks">                                        <div class="left"><a href="/cms/">CME Library</a></div>                                        <div class="left" style="margin-left: 20px"></div>                                        <div style="clear: both;"></div>                                    </div>                                    <br/>                                    <div id="intro-text">                                        <div id="intro-text-title">                                            <img class="curric-logo"                                                 src="/cms/../cmsdata/course_icons/W13-263_HepC_514x240_3.jpg" alt=""                                                 border="0"/>                                            <div class="curric-title">Demonstrating Improvements in the Diagnosis and                                                Treatment of Hepatitis C: A PI CME Program                                            </div>                                        </div>                                        <div class="curric-intro-text">This PI-CME activity was designed to improve your                                            ability to identify and co-manage the care of patients with hepatitis C. In                                            the first stage of the program, you will be able to review your current                                            performance levels based on key measures, compare your practice with those                                            of your peers and national benchmarks, and establish educational and                                            performance-improvement goals. The program intervention—three (3) detailed                                            patient case studies—will demonstrate best practices in implementing                                            recommended screening protocols for hepatitis C and ensuring that infected                                            patients receive appropriate interventions. In the final stage of the                                            activity, you will be able to review your progress based on a number of                                            metrics, which include score improvement, your ranking relative to other                                            clinicians within the provider organization and the national network, and                                            improved clinical performance related to your participation in the                                            educational interventions.                                        </div>                                    </div>                                    <div class="curriculum-record needlogin">                                        <div class="curriculum-record-icon"><img                                                    src="/cms/../cmsdata/course_icons/picme-icon.png"></img></div>                                        <div class="curriculum-record-title">Stage A</div>                                        <div class="curriculum-record-lo"><p>After completing this activity, the                                                participant will demonstrate the ability to:</p>                                            <ol>                                                <li>                                                    Test all patients at risk for HCV infection and document result in                                                    the patient chart                                                </li>                                                <li>                                                    Employ appropriate interventions in patients diagnosed with HCV                                                    prior to referral to specialty care                                                </li>                                                <li>                                                    Understand and counsel infected patients on the risks and benefits                                                    of the available HCV treatment options                                                </li>                                                <li>                                                    Describe strategies for improving HCV treatment compliance                                                </li>                                                <ol>                                        </div>                                    </div>                                    <div style='clear: both'></div>                                    <div class="curriculum-record needlogin">                                        <div class="curriculum-record-icon"><img                                                    src="/cms/../cmsdata/course_icons/hepcman.png"></img></div>                                        <div class="curriculum-record-title">Implementing Birth-Cohort Screening for                                            Hepatitis C Virus                                        </div>                                        <div class="curriculum-record-lo"><p>After completing this activity, the                                                participant will demonstrate the ability to:</p>                                            <ol>                                                <li>Discuss the rationale for &quot;birth-cohort&quot; screening for HCV                                                    infection                                                </li>                                                <li>                                                    Describe the recommended steps that primary care providers should                                                    take when a patient screens positive for HCV infection                                                </li>                                                <ol>                                        </div>                                    </div>                                    <div style='clear: both'></div>                                    <div class="curriculum-record needlogin">                                        <div class="curriculum-record-icon"><img                                                    src="/cms/../cmsdata/course_icons/32-women.png"></img></div>                                        <div class="curriculum-record-title">A 32-Year-Old Woman With Chronic, Untreated                                            Hepatitis C Infection                                        </div>                                        <div class="curriculum-record-lo"><p>After completing this activity, the                                                participant will demonstrate the ability to:</p>                                            <ol>                                                <li>Discuss the importance of HCV RNA screening in patients who have                                                    screened positive for HCV antibodies                                                </li>                                                <li>Identify potential barriers to patient adherence to HCV therapy</li>                                                <ol>                                        </div>                                    </div>                                    <div style='clear: both'></div>                                    <div class="curriculum-record needlogin">                                        <div class="curriculum-record-icon"><img                                                    src="/cms/../cmsdata/course_icons/hcvman.png"></img></div>                                        <div class="curriculum-record-title">Management of a Treatment-Experienced HCV                                            Patient                                        </div>                                        <div class="curriculum-record-lo"><p>After completing this activity, the                                                participant will demonstrate the ability to:</p>                                            <ol>                                                <li>Understand and counsel infected patients on the risks and benefits                                                    of the available HCV treatment options                                                </li>                                                <li>Describe strategies for improving HCV treatment adherence</li>                                                <ol>                                        </div>                                    </div>                                    <div style='clear: both'></div>                                    <div class="curriculum-record needlogin">                                        <div class="curriculum-record-icon"><img                                                    src="/cms/../cmsdata/course_icons/picme-icon_1.png"></img></div>                                        <div class="curriculum-record-title">Stage C</div>                                        <div class="curriculum-record-lo"><p>After completing this activity, the                                                participant will demonstrate the ability to:</p>                                            <ol>                                                <li>                                                    Test all patients at risk for HCV infection and document result in                                                    the patient chart                                                </li>                                                <li>                                                    Employ appropriate interventions in patients diagnosed with HCV                                                    prior to referral to specialty care                                                </li>                                                <li>                                                    Understand and counsel infected patients on the risks and benefits                                                    of the available HCV treatment options                                                </li>                                                <li>                                                    Describe strategies for improving HCV treatment compliance                                                </li>                                                <ol>                                        </div>                                    </div>                                    <div style='clear: both'></div>                                </div>                            </div> <!-- /node-inner, /node --> </div> <!-- --> </div>                </div> <!-- /#content-inner, /#content -->                <div id="sidebar-right">                    <div id="sidebar-right-inner">                        <div id="altcontainer2">                            <div id="companionlogo"><img                                        src="/cms/sites/all/themes/zen/duke-picmetheme/img/logo-companion.gif"                                        id="logo-companion" alt="CMECompanion" class=""/></div>                            <!-- Accordion Menu Start -->                            <div id="list1">                                <div id="block-cmeprofile-1"                                     class="block block-cmeprofile region-odd odd region-count-1 count-1">                                    <div class="block-inner">                                        <div class="content"> 